main event: A white and silver oblong-shaped object with knobs and bumps observed at Fallon Navy Station, Nevada in 1956.
interesting points: The object was estimated to be at an altitude of 20,000 ft and traveling at a speed of 1,000 mph.
It was observed for a duration of 25 seconds before flying out of sight.
The observation suggested that the object was an aircraft in dive and possibly a new configuration undergoing testing.
The report indicated that the cause of the sighting was unknown.
The document was sourced from the military, indicating that it was a credible witness account.
